UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Kevin DAVIS, also known as Bookman Davis, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-30446

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 18, 2009. Maurice Landrieu, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Eastern District of Louisiana, New Orleans, LA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Sarah Elizabeth Stone, Federal Public Defender’s Office, Eastern District of Louisiana, New Orleans, LA, for Defendants Appellant. Before HIGGINBOTHAM, DENNIS, and PRADO, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Kevin Davis has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Davis has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th CiR. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir R. 47.5.4.
